Class JoinStreamlet<K,R,S,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twitter.heron.streamlet.impl.StreamletImpl<KeyValue<KeyedWindow<K>,T>>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamlet<KeyValue<KeyedWindow<K>,T>>

    public final class JoinStreamlet<K,R,S,T>
extends StreamletImpl<KeyValue<KeyedWindow<K>,T>>
    JoinStreamlet represents a KVStreamlet that is the result of joining two KVStreamlets left and right using a WindowConfig. For all left and right tuples in the window whose keys match, the user supplied joinFunction is applied on the values to get the resulting value. JoinStreamlet's elements are of KeyValue type where the key is KeyWindowInfo type and the value is of type VR.
